<pre><code>&lt;filesMatch "^(?&lt;!index)\.(html|htm|js|css)$"&gt;   FileETag None   &lt;ifModule mod_headers.c&gt;      Header set Cache-Control "max-age=0, no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate"   &lt;/ifModule&gt; &lt;/filesMatch&gt;  &lt;filesMatch "^(index)\.(html)$"&gt;   FileETag None   &lt;ifModule mod_headers.c&gt;      Header set Cache-Control "max-age=0, no-cache, must-revalidate"   &lt;/ifModule&gt; &lt;/filesMatch&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I couldn't find an example for <code>&lt;filesMatch&gt;</code> to check for a specific filename outside of the pattern that follows the tag, so I what I have now is one filesMatch to set headers for everything besides index.html and one just for index.html to set the headers without no-store. </p>  <p>This seems redundant, so I was wondering if there was a better way to do this?</p>